		<div class="w3-content" style="max-width:1100px;margin-top:50px;margin-bottom:60px">
			<div class = "w3-panel w3-center">
				<h1 class = "display-1"  id = "top_spacing" style="margin-top: 10%; font-size: 6em; font-weight: bold;">Help</h1>
				<div style = "overflow: auto">
					<h2 class = "w3-xxlarge" id = "top_spacing">Sign Up</h2>
					<p class = "w3-xlarge">
						Once you sign up, you will be redirected to the login page. If this happens then your account was created successfully. Enter the required information and login.
					</p>
					<h2 class = "w3-xxlarge">Home Page</h2>
					<p class = "w3-xlarge">
						Your disposable income is the amount of money you can spend freely. This amount is the income that is entered through the set income button on the wages page. The new purchase button lets you quickly enter a purchase that made. When you enter a new purchase, the cost will be deducted from your current disposable income and your new disposable income will be updated and displayed. 
					</p>
					<h2 class = "w3-xxlarge">Wages</h2>
					<p class = "w3-xlarge">
						This page is for setting up your income. You set this by pressing the set income button, entering the amount, and then submitting it. The add expenditure button is for adding frequent expenditures such as utility bills but are not limited to these. This page will also update the amount of disposable income available on the home page.
					</p>
					<h2 class = "w33-xxlarge">Goals</h2>
					<p class = "w3-xlarge">
						Here a user can add different goals that they have. So if there is something you want that you don't have enough money, you can turn it into a goal and save up towards that goal. To enter a goal, hit the new goal button, enter the required information, and hit add goal. The goal will the be displayed on the page.
					</p>
				</div>
